            The noble and learned Lord is quite right: the amendment does not march on that issue at all. The point of difference that he has correctly identified between us is simply that I am saying that the issue is too important for it to become permissive towards the Information Commissioner as to whether he makes a report. I am certain that I shall need to return to the matter on Report, but I beg leave to withdraw the amendment.</p><p>
